codeigniter-scaffold

	Generates simple cruds for codeiginiter 2.

	1. Usage:

		./generate.rb scaffold <model> field1:string field2:text ...

		<model> is the table/model name for database
		- Valid types:
			* string
			* text
	
	2. It will create some files at:

		* application/controller/<model>.php
		* application/migrations/create_<model>.php
		* application/models/<model>_model.php
		* application/views/<model>/create.php
		* appplication/views/<model>/index.php

	3. Add to codeiginiter:

		a. Executes the migration at your database by:
			 mysql -uroot -p <database_name> < create_<model>.sql

		b. copy/paste 'application' folder at your 'application' folder of codeginiter

		c. access the url of your generated crud:
				127.0.0.1/project_name/index.php/<model>/

	4. Have fun!

	Notes:
		* Every scaffold will create 'id', 'created_at', 'updated_at' columns;
		* Id is an auto_increment field;
		* You can see an scaffold example at 'application' folder of this repo.
